<span id="freeTextContainer14419265622169450954">I read the English translation. I&apos;m sure if I read the French version I would give this 5 stars.<br/><br/>This is an amazing story with a different viewpoint specially because one doesn&apos;t accept common humanity or collaborate it with the German soldiers in WWII setting. The story is about a German soldier who loves France, its culture, and loves everything passionately. But he is in France as the conqueror/ the enemy. <br/><br/>Best part about this novel is that we get to witness France&apos;s WWII occupation through th</span>
  <span id="freeText14419265622169450954" style="display:none">I read the English translation. I'm sure if I read the French version I would give this 5 stars.<br /><br />This is an amazing story with a different viewpoint specially because one doesn't accept common humanity or collaborate it with the German soldiers in WWII setting. The story is about a German soldier who loves France, its culture, and loves everything passionately. But he is in France as the conqueror/ the enemy. <br /><br />Best part about this novel is that we get to witness France's WWII occupation through the eyes of a Frenchman who had written this during the occupation. WWII Nazis are portrayed throughout history only as monsters. Bur in this, it's less prejudiced, more honest. We get to see both Germany, and France through a different perspective.<br /><br />It also allows the reader to look at love in a different viewpoint, whether it is romantic or patriotic. <br /><br />This is absolutely a good read!</span>
