    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_947643810" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/947643810" />
    <a title="Czarny Pies" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies"><img alt="Czarny Pies" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400687408p2/29160274.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/947643810?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Czarny Pies" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Czarny Pies" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies">Czarny Pies</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">French history buffs</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Czarny by: </span>
      My father
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29160274-czarny-pies?shelf=french-lit">french-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer947643810" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10630456763181630092">This collection of short stories written by a French resistance fighter was a wild success in France and around the world when it was released in the 1940s. The stories are for the most part bleak. They concern people who live constantly with the threat of imminent death and ask themselves big questions about making morally correct but highly dangerous decisions.<br/><br/>This book has aged badly. One naturally admires Vercors for the personal courage he demonstrated but his moralizing now seems tiresome </span>
  <span id="freeText10630456763181630092" style="display:none">This collection of short stories written by a French resistance fighter was a wild success in France and around the world when it was released in the 1940s. The stories are for the most part bleak. They concern people who live constantly with the threat of imminent death and ask themselves big questions about making morally correct but highly dangerous decisions.<br /><br />This book has aged badly. One naturally admires Vercors for the personal courage he demonstrated but his moralizing now seems tiresome to people living during safer times.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10630456763181630092" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

