    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1669288338?book_show_action=true">Jun 15, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Masanaka Takashima" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Masanaka Takashima" href="/user/show/1463040-masanaka-takashima">Masanaka Takashima</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780854963782" href="/book/show/332544.The_Silence_of_the_Sea_Le_Silence_de_la_mer">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1669288338&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1669288338" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1852119631649362815">I read this in Japanese translation. This classic story has a French family that billets an occupying and stationing German army officer who is highly cultured and doesn&apos;t seem like a Nazi party member. While this German talks a lot -- about his love for French literature, his original occupation as composer and so on, the owner of the house talks when he needs to and his young niece talks nothing. The German occupant sounds modest in a way, but the house owners&apos; silence is so grave and unforgiv</span>
  <span id="freeText1852119631649362815" style="display:none">I read this in Japanese translation. This classic story has a French family that billets an occupying and stationing German army officer who is highly cultured and doesn't seem like a Nazi party member. While this German talks a lot -- about his love for French literature, his original occupation as composer and so on, the owner of the house talks when he needs to and his young niece talks nothing. The German occupant sounds modest in a way, but the house owners' silence is so grave and unforgiving, making German guy's sympathetic gesture look nothing but hypocritical. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1852119631649362815" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


