<div id="review_1920274985" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1920274985" />
    <a title="Francisca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11397652-francisca"><img alt="Francisca" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493050691p2/11397652.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1920274985?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Francisca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Francisca" href="/user/show/11397652-francisca">Francisca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789722313889" href="/book/show/15923954-o-sil-ncio-do-mar">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Francisca by: </span>
      Bli
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11397652-francisca?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11397652-francisca?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1920274985" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13870640197837340041">During the Occupation of France in WWII, a French family, composed of an elderly father and his grown-up daughter, takes a vow of silence before the occupying German who comes to stay in their house. Every evening he sits in their parlor and begins speaking with his silent hosts. The result is this poignant, subtle reflection on war, peace, the importance of culture, and love. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


