  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4048001172" />
    <a title="Abasifreke Ekpe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100756074-abasifreke-ekpe"><img alt="Abasifreke Ekpe" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1622230966p2/100756074.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4048001172?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Abasifreke Ekpe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Abasifreke Ekpe" href="/user/show/100756074-abasifreke-ekpe">Abasifreke Ekpe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780854963782" href="/book/show/332544.The_Silence_of_the_Sea_Le_Silence_de_la_mer">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4048001172" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18439836064195691376">This was a quick and easy read about the German occupation in France during World War II. It is told in the first person point of view of the uncle, where the 3 main characters (and only characters) are the uncle, niece, and the occupying German soldier. This is a fictional story of French resistance, but as it was published in 1942 around the time when France was occupied, I imagine the characters’ thoughts and feelings are reflective of the thoughts and feelings of those who lived during that </span>
  <span id="freeText18439836064195691376" style="display:none">This was a quick and easy read about the German occupation in France during World War II. It is told in the first person point of view of the uncle, where the 3 main characters (and only characters) are the uncle, niece, and the occupying German soldier. This is a fictional story of French resistance, but as it was published in 1942 around the time when France was occupied, I imagine the characters’ thoughts and feelings are reflective of the thoughts and feelings of those who lived during that time. It is sad, yet moving, with romantic undertones. Overall, a good read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="18439836064195691376" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


