<div id="review_1330193127" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1330193127" />
    <a title="Spencer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2706803-spencer"><img alt="Spencer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1252532807p2/2706803.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1330193127?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Spencer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Spencer" href="/user/show/2706803-spencer">Spencer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780854963782" href="/book/show/332544.The_Silence_of_the_Sea_Le_Silence_de_la_mer">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2706803-spencer?shelf=foreign">foreign</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2706803-spencer?shelf=novella">novella</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2706803-spencer?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1330193127" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer666167212518620344">Many consider Vercors little book one of the best pieces of literature to come out WWII France. One might argue whether this is a short story, novella or novel because of its brevity. I would say that the complexity of its subject matter makes it at least a novella. I might add that The Silence of the Sea is essential reading for anyone wanting to study the non-Vichy French point of view during WWII.<p> Its underground publication alone is a wonderful background story, which is covered very well in</p></span>
  <span id="freeText666167212518620344" style="display:none">Many consider Vercors little book one of the best pieces of literature to come out WWII France. One might argue whether this is a short story, novella or novel because of its brevity. I would say that the complexity of its subject matter makes it at least a novella. I might add that The Silence of the Sea is essential reading for anyone wanting to study the non-Vichy French point of view during WWII.<p> Its underground publication alone is a wonderful background story, which is covered very well in the introductory comments. Also crucial is understanding how the French intelligentsia saw itself and how it related to the rest of the world during WWII. Vercors uses the Beauty and the Beast metaphor to highlight the relationship between the Germans and the French. The French reaction to the Germans was basically one of ignoring them, as if they were invisible. The French would never initiate a conversation, and those initiated by the Germans were met with silence. </p><p>Vercors introduces the complication of a German officer who is a composer, lover of art, and an admirer of anything French. The conflict comes when we examine the benefits he sees coming from this new-found German/French relationship—he considers it a "marriage"—and contrast them with what the true German goal is. Add an unexpected romantic element, and you have a very rich and tender story.</p></span>
  <a data-text-id="666167212518620344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

