<div id="review_1999969892" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1999969892" />
    <a title="Pamela" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/143523-pamela"><img alt="Pamela" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1999969892?book_show_action=true">May 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pamela" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pamela" href="/user/show/143523-pamela">Pamela</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1999969892" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12321838862604638686">&quot;The Silence of the Sea&quot;. Considered one of the most important books to be published underground by the French Resistance during WWII. A novella really -- very short -- but my edition had also an Historical Introduction and also a Literary Introduction, which were important reading for the historical context as well as some of the controversy and symbolism of the book. <br/><br/>Resistance by silence. A household occupied by a German officer refuses to acknowledge his presence as a form of non-collaborati</span>
  <span id="freeText12321838862604638686" style="display:none">"The Silence of the Sea". Considered one of the most important books to be published underground by the French Resistance during WWII. A novella really -- very short -- but my edition had also an Historical Introduction and also a Literary Introduction, which were important reading for the historical context as well as some of the controversy and symbolism of the book. <br /><br />Resistance by silence. A household occupied by a German officer refuses to acknowledge his presence as a form of non-collaboration. But they nonetheless impact one another profoundly. Ultimately, though, even this "good German" who loves France and has hopes for German-French unity and a greater Europe, cannot resist what he himself sees as the innate German character. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12321838862604638686" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


