    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3787295522" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3787295522" />
    <a title="Virginia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21304267-virginia"><img alt="Virginia" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3787295522?book_show_action=true">Feb 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Virginia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Virginia" href="/user/show/21304267-virginia">Virginia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3787295522" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3293601686073913450">Vercors&apos; short stories are written in a simple, direct style that strikes right to the heart of the reader and they depict perfectly the dramatic years of the German occupation of France during WW2. <br/><br/>The emotions of the characters - their anger, their pain, their suffering, their horror, their powerlessness - are so well written that the reader can almost feel as if they were thrown back in time, silent spectators in a corner of the room.<br/><br/>In the otherwise pleasant setting of &quot;Ce jour-là&quot;, a father</span>
  <span id="freeText3293601686073913450" style="display:none">Vercors' short stories are written in a simple, direct style that strikes right to the heart of the reader and they depict perfectly the dramatic years of the German occupation of France during WW2. <br /><br />The emotions of the characters - their anger, their pain, their suffering, their horror, their powerlessness - are so well written that the reader can almost feel as if they were thrown back in time, silent spectators in a corner of the room.<br /><br />In the otherwise pleasant setting of "Ce jour-là", a father and a small boy going for a walk in the woods, we can feel a mounting sense of distress and anxiety. "Le Songe" is capable of describing that feeling of detachment from horrors felt so far away from our reality and, at the same time, it brings to life the unfathomable reality of concentration camps better than a movie ever could.<br /><br />The strength of the emotions shown in "L'impuissance" and in "L'imprimerie de Verdun" is in stark contrast with the stoic silence of the characters from "Le Silence de la mer", and yet all together they give a perfect portrait of what the author and the people around him felt during those years.<br /><br />A must-read that will make you travel back in time and will leave you with a heavy heart.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3293601686073913450" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


